  "texts": [
    "In practice, this corresponds to performing a full on-policy update.",
    "The Bin history (BH)replay buffer sorts sequences into bins with respect to their reward.",
    "It consists of the following fixed binds with respect to rewards: [0, 0.1], (0.1, 0.2], …, (0.9, 1].",
    "For the off-policy algorithms, the buffer also includes a bin storing invalid SMILES strings, i.e., SMILES string with a score -1.",
    "Each bin has a maximum size of 1000 sequences."
  ],
